## Three Themes
1. Progressive Disclosure — tiered context loading (Essential/Situational/Never-Needed)
2. Model-Task Fit — match model capability to task complexity  
3. Path Safety — scope-restrict agent filesystem access

## 2-Pass Dispatch Discipline (merged from TKT-0313)
Platform-wide rule: No executor receives undiscovered work.
Any agent dispatching to any agent MUST separate discovery from execution.
NOT Yoda-only — applies to Aria→Spark, Forge→self, Cron→agent, etc.

